  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HIAS Sexual and Gender Based Violence Prevention and Response Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. staff in each of the 11 camps will conduct nine preventive gender based violence related activities, workshops, trainings and drama each quarter that address GBV dynamics, causes, consequences, and methods of community mobilization. 
2. children and youth attending school are sensitized via focus group discussions on Sexual Exploitation and Abuse (SEA) 
3. married couples are provided with four sessions (quarterly) of family sensitization and counseling through a door-to-door campaign against domestic violence.   
4. community mobilizers trained each quarter on how to respond to the needs of survivors of SGBV, the referral services available at the camp level as well as the guiding principle for working with SGBV survivors, and increase their skills as demonstrated by the quarterly number of cases identified, referred and followed up by them. 
5. victims of domestic violence in the camps are provided with at least two sessions of individual counseling and benefit from four home visits 
6. work therapy  - tailoring, knitting, kitchen gardening &#x2013; for adult and adolescent SGBV survivors
7. weekly sessions of play therapy for adolescent and children SGBV survivors
8. knitting, soap making and baking activities for single mothers in 11 camps
9. refugee male head of households are sensitized via weekly focus group 
discussions on women&#x2019;s and girls&#x2019; rights and demonstrate an understanding by creating a voluntary committee in each camp to promote and protect these rights.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Refugees, vulnerable victims of torture/sexual and gender based violence</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To maintain a sustainable advocacy network and community based referral system to identify and  prevent Gender Based Violence (GBV) and Sexual Exploitation and Abuse (SEA),  to respond to sexual violence and intimate partner violence by providing psychosocial support to survivors, and to encourage women&#x2019;s and girls&#x2019; self reliance, leadership and decision making ability in the community.</narrative>
  </description>
